{"key":"processedPost-13547535","value":{"id":13547535,"first":13544953,"last":25428748,"when":1290878797,"utime":"11/27/10 07:26 PM","cleanedPost":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><strong>Fungal growth said:</strong><br />p.s.: they will pin when they feel they are at the end of thier life, i.e. when all the food is ate up.</blockquote><br />Not so.&nbsp; When all the food is gone, the mycelium dies.&nbsp; It pins when it's fully colonized and exposed to fresh air and bright light.&nbsp; Mushrooms don't form at the end of the mycelium life, they form at the peak of it.<br />You're right about the other though, the mantra to colonize in total darkness is bad advice and totally incorrect.&nbsp; It's a relic of an age when mushroom growing was in its infancy and not well understood.<br />RR"}}